1. ECG (AD8232)

Normal: Stable sinus rhythm (60–100 bpm, no irregular peaks).

Warning: Arrhythmia suspicion (irregular R-R intervals, tachycardia >100 bpm, bradycardia <60 bpm).

Critical: Ventricular fibrillation, prolonged tachycardia (>150 bpm), or absent signal.

(ECG is analyzed by the AI model, but these ranges are good for rule-based checks[if the model doesn't work at all].)

2. Heart Rate (MAX30102, HR output)

Normal: 60–100 bpm (resting adults).

Warning: 100–120 bpm (mild tachycardia) OR 50–59 bpm (mild bradycardia).

Critical: <50 bpm or >120 bpm (severe brady/tachycardia).

3. SpO₂ (MAX30102, oxygen saturation)

Normal: 95–100%.

Warning: 91–94% (mild hypoxemia).

Critical: ≤90% (severe hypoxemia, medical emergency).

4. Blood Pressure (MPX5050DP + algorithm)

(approx. converted into clinical categories)

Normal: SBP 90–120 mmHg, DBP 60–80 mmHg.

Warning:

Pre-hypertension: SBP 121–139 OR DBP 81–89.

Hypotension: SBP 80–89 OR DBP <60.

Critical:

Hypertension stage 2: SBP ≥160 OR DBP ≥100.

Severe hypotension: SBP <80.

5. Body Temperature (DS18B20, skin contact)

Normal: 36.0–37.5 °C.

Warning:

Mild hypothermia: 35–35.9 °C.

Low-grade fever: 37.6–38.0 °C.

Critical:

Hypothermia: <35 °C.

High fever: >38.0 °C.

6. Ambient Temperature & Humidity (DHT22)

Normal: 20–30 °C, 30–60% RH.

Warning: 10–19 °C OR 31–40 °C (cold/heat stress zone).

Critical: <10 °C OR >40 °C, humidity >85% (extreme conditions).

7. UV Radiation (ML8511)

Normal: UV index 0–2 (safe).

Warning: UV index 3–5 (moderate risk).

Critical: UV index ≥6 (high risk of skin/eye damage).

8. Galvanic Skin Response (GSR)

(depends on baseline, relative measurement)

Normal: Low conductivity (resting baseline).

Warning: 20–40% increase over baseline (stress onset, mild fatigue).

Critical: >40% increase over baseline (severe stress, dehydration risk).

9. Electromyography (EMG)

Normal: Expected low-to-moderate muscle activity at rest.

Warning: Sustained abnormal spikes or tremors (indicative of fatigue/stress).

Critical: Continuous abnormal high activity (possible muscle seizure, severe fatigue).
